Honestly, apart from security, which I’d call the number one priority, I think the value of a blockchain mainly comes down to three things:
Decentralization, to avoid or at least limit any kind of manipulation;
Scalability, so the network can handle a solid amount of transactions and open up more earning potential for the protocol;
Adoption, meaning how many people actually use it and how many transactions are happening — that’s what really drives revenue in the long run.
So where does ZINK fit in all this? Personally, I think ZINK has a lot of potential and could have a great future ahead.

Considering that it was a live stream of just over 24 hours, the average number of viewers remained very stable throughout the event, but this is due to a number of factors:
1 - We had double XP;
2 - In each match I was giving 1000 Atlas to the first place winner (more than 190,000 Atlas in prizes throughout the entire event);
3 - We had some Iris Blessing codes that were being distributed to the viewers.

If it were a tournament, the viewership would be even higher, as it was in Gateway Defense or Sogmian Flame.

